<br>
Pog is better than Hate because:<br>
<br>
1).  It costs 105pp per group to port into Hate.  And you might zone up and find the plane empty of monsters and drops.<br>
2).  The Hate break still carries a small degree of danger, but even a gnome could run a successful PoG break. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yaenbzhen>YaenBzhen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/10/03 1:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Armor</span><hr size=1> <blockquote style="padding-left:0.5em; margin-left:0; margin-right:0; margin-top:0; margin-bottom:0; border-left:solid 2">2) Give examples of the Old Planar Armor, and where the PoK NPC's are for turn in.</blockquote><br>
<br>
From PoH:<br>
<br>
<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=2387" target="_new">Indicolite Breastplate</a><br>
<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=5230" target="_new">Legionaire's Scale Breastplate</a><br>
<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=2046" target="_new">Rune Etched Chestplate</a><br>
<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=2048" target="_new">Woven Shadow Chestplate</a><br>
<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=2050" target="_new">Ethereal Mist Breastplate</a><br>
<br>
... to name a few. Each class has a full set. Warrior, Cleric, and Shaman (Indicolite, Ethereal Mist, Rune Etched/Scaled Hierophant) are probably the most common drops on the first floor.<br>
<br>
As for where to turn them in, I believe you can use any class trainer. As for where those folks are... Verant has recently sanctioned the use of ShowEQ in game with the Backspace key. I'd suggest you get at that. :)<br>
